tween the source and knowledge file, so that's confirmed. I think I have everything I need to finalize my analysis now.\n\nLooking at the omissions more carefully, the definitions explaining what low and high resolution mean in this context—essentially standard displays versus retina displays—would be helpful context, but the actual implementation details are all accounted for. The threshold value and image paths are there. I'd say these are minor gaps rather than critical ones.\n\nThe remaining omissions are also minor: the explanation about why 1.25 is used as the boundary value since no actual devices have a pixel ratio below that, and the CSS class identifier `nablarch_ResponsibleImage` isn't mentioned in the hints. Overall, the knowledge file covers the essential implementation information quite well.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18644,"cache_read_input_tokens":35069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18644,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8c55577-d2bc-4f79-a55f-9f6bbc4a0671","uuid":"c31f0f1b-24f7-48ae-a4c8-5f77139cea7a"}
